The paper proposes a new routing protocol for mobile ad-hoc networks, which is a subfield of computer networking and falls under the cs.NI (Networks and Internet Architecture) category. The paper also involves the use of algorithms and data structures for constructing and maintaining routing tables, which could fall under the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) category. The paper also discusses the performance evaluation of the proposed protocol, which could fall under the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) category. The paper also involves the use of GPS and energy-aware selection of gateway nodes, which could fall under the cs.IT (Information Theory) category. Finally, the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques for predicting the energy levels of nodes, which could fall under the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category.
